/// datboi:transform@1 — the transform lane (D89 epoch, ruled 2026-07-14).
///
/// The streaming interaction model proven by the M2 exit test (a 3.9 GiB
/// zip member replayed in bounded memory, verified sequentially and
/// through seeked ranges): the guest PULLS inputs and PUSHES outputs.
/// `run` executes to completion, calling `source.read` / `file.read-at`
/// on host-implemented input resources and `sink.write` on
/// host-implemented output resources. Multi-input transforms read
/// whichever input they need next; the host never has to guess.
///
/// There is no whole-buffer sibling in this epoch (D89): a buffered
/// transform is a guest that reads all, computes, writes all — the
/// `datboi-guest-transform` crate ships that as a ten-line adapter. The
/// host never consumed a "definitely not streaming" signal; the planner's
/// inputs are the descriptor's seek class and random-access declarations.
///
/// Determinism contract (D5), two layers:
///
/// 1. The only imports are `datboi:streams/types@1` — host-implemented
///    resources, nothing ambient (D46). See that package for the exact
///    read/write contract that keeps backpressure unobservable.
/// 2. Fuel meters guest instructions only; host time inside stream calls
///    is free and irrelevant to guest-visible state.
///
/// Vocabulary rides in canonical CBOR, not wit types (D89): `params` is
/// the recipe's canonical-CBOR params bstr verbatim (the op owns its
/// schema), and `describe` RETURNS a canonical-CBOR descriptor —
/// `{1: seek-class, 2: random-access-inputs}`, schema documented in
/// `datboi-guest-transform` beside the encoders. Record/enum growth is
/// schema evolution, never an ABI break. Added keys must be
/// ADVISORY-ONLY: old hosts ignore unknown keys (D64 — newer components
/// run under older cores), so anything a host must understand to execute
/// correctly is a lane version, never a new key.
///
/// Versioning (docs/worlds.md): every published version is immutable
/// forever. Additive imports and probed exports are minors; any shape
/// change is a major and the old major's host linker lives forever.
package datboi:transform@1.0.0;

interface types {
    use datboi:streams/types@1.0.0.{source, file};

    /// One resolved recipe input, in recipe order.
    variant input {
        /// Sequential pull stream.
        sequential(source),
        /// Random access (declared in the descriptor).
        random-access(file),
    }
}

world transform {
    use types.{input};
    use datboi:streams/types@1.0.0.{sink};

    /// Describe an operation's capabilities as a canonical-CBOR
    /// descriptor (schema above). Must be pure and constant for a given
    /// `op` — the host may cache the result by component hash. Unknown
    /// ops are errors (refusal has a polite path everywhere, D89).
    export describe: func(op: string) -> result<list<u8>, string>;

    /// Apply one operation: read `inputs` (recipe order), write the
    /// claimed outputs to `outputs` (recipe order). Runs to completion.
    /// The host verifies every output hash against the recipe (D4), so a
    /// buggy transform wastes CPU but cannot corrupt the store.
    export run: func(
        op: string,
        params: list<u8>,
        inputs: list<input>,
        outputs: list<sink>,
    ) -> result<_, string>;

    /// Produce exactly `output[output-ix][offset .. offset+len)` into
    /// `out` — the range-serving path for non-opaque transforms (D49).
    /// ALL inputs arrive as `random-access` here regardless of the
    /// descriptor (serving a range implies the host already has seekable
    /// sources — materialized if necessary, per the spill rule);
    /// the descriptor's random-access declarations govern `run` only.
    /// Writing fewer than `len` bytes is legal only where the output
    /// ends inside the range. MUST byte-match the same span of a full
    /// `run` materialization: the conformance gate property-tests this
    /// with boundary-straddling ranges, and production range reads
    /// verify against the output bao outboard (D49) — a mismatch
    /// quarantines the component's seekability, it never serves bytes.
    /// Opaque ops return an error here.
    export serve-range: func(
        op: string,
        params: list<u8>,
        inputs: list<input>,
        output-ix: u32,
        offset: u64,
        len: u64,
        out: sink,
    ) -> result<_, string>;
}
